Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, significant proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, with low urine specific gravity and brown, cloudy urine. These findings suggest impaired renal function, possible nephrotic syndrome or diabetic ketoacidosis, though HbA1c is unexpectedly low. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Recommend urgent clinical correlation for acute or chronic kidney disease and further evaluation of metabolic status.
